  "prompt": "Can I be pregnant while having a missed period?",
  "response": "Yes, a missed period is often one of the first signs of pregnancy. When you become pregnant, your body starts producing hormones that can prevent menstruation. However, there are other reasons for a missed period, such as stress, changes in weight, hormonal imbalances, and certain medical conditions. If you suspect you might be pregnant, it is a good idea to take a home pregnancy test or consult a healthcare provider to confirm.",
